
[1]scioptic

   SCIOP'TIC, a. [Gr. shadow and to see.]

   Pertaining to the camera obscura, or to the art of exhibiting images
   through a hole in a darkened room.

   SCIOP'TIC, n. A sphere or globe with a lens made to turn like the eye;
                used in experiments with the camera obscura.
